08/04/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The government will host a trilateral meeting of the signatories of the Adriatic Charter in May, says Neven Jurica, head of parliament's foreign affairs committee. 
The signatories are Albania, Macedonia and Croatia, with the United States as a partner. 
Skopje hosted the first meeting last year.
In other news, foreign ministry officials of Croatia, Italy and Slovenia met in the Croatian town of Pula on Wednesday (7 April) to discuss trilateral co-operation in environmental protection and sustainable fisheries. 
They also tackled economic management of maritime resources.
Also Wednesday, the interior ministry announced plans to implement a police reform project with the help of the OSCE. 
The goal is to bring police force management into line with European standards. 
(HINA - 07/04/04)
